Title: AMD takes aim at Intel with new 96-core Threadripper 9000 series CPU
Description:
AMD has announced its latest Zen 5-based Ryzen Threadripper 9000 Series of CPUs at Computex today.
The 9000 Series and 9000 WX-Series are built for the demanding workstation market, and the top Threadripper Pro 9995WX will ship with 96 cores and 192 threads.

Title: South Africa's president heads to the White House. Can he charm Trump?

Title: The great battery race: China and the U.S. compete over the future of EVs
Description:
The car you drive years in the future might run off a battery being invented in a lab today.

Description:

Title: Not quite the American dream: Renting is becoming a better deal, even if you're wealthy or a retiree

Title: How much does AI cost? Here are the industry averages
